KPM System Architecture Document
Version: 1.0
Document Type: System Architecture Specification

1. Introduction
Purpose
This document defines the overall architecture of KPM (Kapuletu Project Manager).
It explains how the platform is structured, how different parts of the system interact, how users move through the application, and how engineering work flows from project creation to product release.
Rather than focusing on implementation details, this document defines the logical architecture of the system.

2. Architectural Philosophy
KPM is designed around one central principle:
Everything exists within the context of a Project.
Unlike traditional project management tools where tasks, meetings, files and discussions are scattered across independent modules, KPM treats the Project as the center of the entire engineering process.
Every object belongs to a project.
Everything is connected.

3. System Hierarchy
The complete hierarchy is intentionally simple.
Organization
    │
    ├── Members
    │
    └── Projects
            │
            ├── Team
            ├── Roadmap
            ├── Modules
            ├── Sprints
            ├── Meetings
            ├── Documents
            ├── Activity
            └── Releases
Inside every Module
Module
    │
    └── Features
            │
            ├── Deliverables
            ├── Reviews
            ├── Daily Updates
            ├── Comments
            └── Attachments
Nothing exists outside this structure.

4. User Hierarchy
KPM has only four levels of users.
Level 1 — Platform Administrator
Responsible for the KPM platform itself.
Responsibilities
Manage organizations
Platform configuration
Platform security
Platform maintenance

Level 2 — Organization Administrator
Represents Kapuletu Management.
Responsibilities
Create Project Managers
Create organization standards
View all projects
View reports
Manage organization members

Level 3 — Project Manager
Owns one or more projects.
Responsible for
Project setup
Team management
Product planning
Sprint planning
Reviews
Meetings
Approvals
Delivery

Level 4 — Team Member
Examples
Backend Engineer
Frontend Engineer
UI Designer
QA
DevOps
Their workspace only contains work assigned to them.

