These integrations are lightweight references rather than full synchronizations, keeping the system simple and focused.

25. Architectural Principles
Every design decision in KPM should follow these principles:
Projects are the center of the system.
Features are the primary unit of engineering work.
Every object has a clear owner.
Work should be traceable from planning to release.
The interface should expose only what each role needs.
Context should never be lost—related information stays linked.
Integrate with external engineering tools instead of rebuilding them.
Keep workflows opinionated enough to encourage consistency, but flexible enough to fit different projects.

